1 This is, beyond doubt, the Thomas de Hastings who grants the confirma- tion printed as No. XXXI. in the Whitby Chartulary. He was the son of Hugh de Hastinges, who married Helena, daughter of Alan son of Thorphin de Allerston. The names of Gilbert de Aton and William Buscel, present here in sequence to Thomas de Hastings' name, are both appended to the charter just named. The connection of John FitzBaldwin de Allerston with Torphin, or his son Alan, is not apparent. Some clue as to his time is gained from the fact that he is a contemporary of Thomas de Hastings. He, Thomas, succeeded his father about 1203.
